# Next.js patterns

## Server vs client

- `'use client'` only when hooks, browser APIs, or event handlers are needed
- `'use server'` actions in colocated `actions.ts` — thin wrappers over services
- After mutations: `revalidatePath('/dashboard/...')`

## Data fetching

- Page hooks: `app/dashboard/<feature>/hooks/use*.ts`
- Shared logic stays in `lib/services/`, not duplicated in pages
- Supabase `.select()` — specify columns; avoid `*` on large tables

## API routes (`app/api/admin/`)

```typescript
export async function POST(request: Request) {
  const staffAuth = await requireStaffApi();
  if ('error' in staffAuth) return staffAuth.error;
  const { supabase } = staffAuth;
  // ...
}
```

## UI conventions

- Tailwind utility classes; `font-bold`, uppercase nav labels, rounded-lg inputs
- Modals: fixed overlay + centered card pattern (see `components/*Modal.tsx`)
- Loading: `Loader2` from lucide with `animate-spin`
- Feedback: `useToast()` from Toast provider

## Types

- Domain types in `lib/types/` — import from there, don't inline duplicates
- Supabase row casts: `data as Profile` after validated queries
